<br>
Max all your abilities for the first 10-15 levels, but after a while you won't be able to afford to keep them all up. An Atrox should probably always max Str and Sta, slnce they're green and you'll want to look for armor that's based on those stats, like Omni-Pol. Try to max Agility because the assault rifle skill depends on it, Sense for ranged energy, and Body Dev for hit points. Put some points in Int because a lot of skills use it, and a little into Psy. Only raise Nano Pool as needed, we only have one or 2 nanos we need to cast in combat.<br>
<br>
Always max Assault Rifle and Ranged Energy; ARs are our weapon of choice, and the best ones are energy weapons. You'll need to keep Fling, Burst, and Full-Auto up, but near as I can tell you only need to get them high enough to meet the requirements on the weapons your using.<br>
<br>
Always max run speed; when you have a Hammer Breeder on your butt as you're crossing Lush Fields, you'll understand why! The other speed stuff is pretty contoversial, no 2 people say the same things. I'd say put some points into Ranged Init; it's not very noticeable, but at high levels you should see a difference in firing speed. As far as the evade stuff goes: some folks say it's useless if you have your aggresion slider set all the way to the right like we all do; some say they're useless unless you keep them close to max; and some say you're crazy to ignore them. You can probably max Dodge, Evade, and Nano Resist for a few levels at least, then decide. I still have no clue. You can ignore Duck, right now that only determines how much damage you take from trapped chests, and you'll have enough hp to take it on the chin. <br>
<br>
Get Elect Eng up to 36 so you can use night vision goggles and floating torches, then leave it alone. Max Comp Lit, you need it for grid access, and adding NCU capacity. Raise Psychology just enough to use any Aggression Enhancers you find; these work like EQ's taunt skill.<br>
<br>
Nanos... well, no one is gonna confuse an Atrox soldier with a nano-tech. Bottom line, only increase these to meet the reqs on a specific nano you want to use. The AC buffs, damage buffs, and reflect shields are useful. Total Mirror Shield used to be our bread &amp; butter, but it was badly nerfed last patch because it was being horribly exploited. Still pretty useful though I think, but others disagree. Besides the soldier specific nanos, there's also useful general nanos that anyone can use that can buff any skill by 10 and 20 points. Max First Aid so you can use the best kits possible, and keep Treatment high to keep down time to a minimum. <br>
<br>
Put some points in Concealment, but don't go nuts. We ain't exactly cat burglars. Get Breaking and Entering up to 30 or so, that seems to be enough to open all chests right now.<br>
<br>
And max Map Nav if you can. It will take a while before you can upload any useful maps, but you'll need them eventually. There's also some map upgrades you can buy; I always get the one that adds an arrow showing the direction you're facing on the map as soon as I can. <br>
